Selko HEP Builder — Changes Summary
Three files updated today — replace all three in GitHub:

selko-hep-styles.css
index.html
selko-hep-app.js


Change 1 — Selko brand colors (selko-hep-styles.css)
Replaced the Metro Mobile warm palette (teal-to-orange) with the Selko brand palette extracted directly from the logo:

Header gradient: #003886 (navy) → #0a7aaf (mid blue) → #23c3bd (teal), left to right
Primary buttons, headings, focus rings: Selko navy #003886
Badges and accents: Selko teal #23c3bd
Compliance badges: #05aca8
Secondary buttons: teal-bg with navy text
Float bar height increased to accommodate two buttons
Small screen breakpoint stacks float bar buttons vertically


Change 2 — Save program without sending (index.html + selko-hep-app.js)
The float bar on the Exercises screen now has two buttons side by side:

View (navy) — opens current program screen as before
💾 Save program (white/navy outline) — new button

Tapping Save opens a modal prompting for a program name. On confirm:

Inserts to hep_programs with a generated code but empty phone (no SMS sent)
Session clears, badge resets to 0
Clinician stays on Exercises screen
Toast confirms save
Program appears in My Programs and can be sent to a patient later via the existing Send flow

Supabase change required for this to work:
Stephen needs to run this in the SQL editor on selko-prod if not already done:
sqlALTER TABLE hep_programs ALTER COLUMN phone DROP NOT NULL;
This allows programs to be saved without a phone number until the clinician is ready to send.

Change 3 — Remove from current program (index.html + selko-hep-app.js)
Already deployed in the previous session but included in these files. When a clinician taps an exercise card that is already in the current session, the popup now shows "Remove from current program" in red instead of "Add to current program." This allows deselection without leaving the exercises screen.

No other backend changes needed beyond the SQL above.
